# Lifeboat Linux (penguins-recovery)

Alpine-based single-file UEFI rescue system. Drop LifeboatLinux.efi into
your EFI System Partition and boot — no USB required.

## Rescue scripts

penguins-recovery shared scripts are in /root/rescue-scripts/:

  chroot-rescue.sh   Mount and chroot into an installed system (LUKS support)
  detect-disks.sh    Show disk layout, LUKS, LVM, and EFI info
  grub-restore.sh    Restore GRUB to MBR or EFI
  password-reset.sh  Reset a Linux user password from rescue
  uefi-repair.sh     Check and repair UEFI boot entries

## User customization

Place scripts in your ESP at:
  EFI/Boot/Lifeboat/UserScripts/

A file named `init` in that directory is sourced on login (keyboard layout,
aliases, custom mounts, etc.).

## Available tools

parted, efibootmgr, gptfdisk, fdisk, lvm2, cryptsetup, dmraid, mdadm,
e2fsprogs, dosfstools, xfsprogs, btrfs-progs, testdisk, nano, vim

## Installing

Copy dist/LifeboatLinux.efi to your ESP:

  cp dist/LifeboatLinux.efi /boot/efi/EFI/Boot/LifeboatLinux.efi

Then add a boot entry or let your firmware discover it.
